rder=0><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Character Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>50 - 60</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Solo/Group</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Solo</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Zone</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Ocean of Tears</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>XP</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>6</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Loot</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>10</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Danger</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>9</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Allizewsaur</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>50</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>-3500 -1000</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Not known</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Lich, Dooming Darkness, Pact of Shadow, Ignite Blood, Invoke Fear, Bond of Death, Augment Death, Steelskin, Dead Man floating</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>A couple points of note I'll mention first:<br><br>

- He hits for dual 137's and bashes for 47, so no matter what its dangerous to do, if something goes wrong or you get a bit of lag you will die FAST.<br>
- I would NOT try this solo without JBoots.<br>
- He also has 14,000 hp, your spell damage is insignificant your pet is going to do 85% + of the damage, if things go well I can kill him in a little under 5 minutes.<br>
- Since your pet's damage is so critical, the better the pet the faster it'll die, and the better your odds.  A 55 is much preferred but a 53 hitter is ok, you can even use a 51 or less but its not worth it.<br><br>

Ok here is the deal, know the timing on your Arch Shielding/Dead man Floating you do NOT want them wearing out in mid-combat.  Put up a Steelskin (if you are more careful use Diamondskin), this extra damage shield has saved my butt a few times, and med to full.<br><br>

Get in Darkness range of Mr. Dino and refresh JBoots, then go lich form.  Augment pet and cast Darkness.  If he doesn't resist, send in pet and Invoke Fear.  If he does resist start running to get some range then stop and Invoke Fear.  If you put enough distance between you and him, you should get it off.  If he resists Fear, repeat till fear sticks, then you have to try to catch him and get a darkness on him.  Once he has both darkness and Fear on him, your pet will already be tearing him up.  Put up an Ignite Blood right away, this is the ONLY damage outside of bond you will do to him as its the most mana efficient, and you can afford to spend some mana.  Start meding.<br><br>

Here is the beauty of this island.  All those little level 10 gobbos running around are going to attack you while meding and interrupt you?  No, they aren't aggressive to you in Lich form!  Know your timing on darkness you NEVER NEVER want it to wear off, if you get the message "Your dooming darkness has worn off" it will always be shortly followed by "Your invoke fear spell has worn off" and now you have a pissed off unslowed level 50 NPC wanting to tear your head off.  Always be sure to cast Darkness early, he has a tendency to resist it A LOT.  I once had him resist it 8 times in a row.  So make sure you keep Darkness/Fear on him.<br><br>

As a note, the reason I use Dooming Darkness vs. Cascading Darkness is first of all much faster casting time, and secondly much lower mana cost.  You are ONLY use this spell for its snare effect, the damage it does is of no consequence.  Engulfing Darkness is faster and lower mana cost but doesn't slow as much or last as long.<br><br>

At around 60% health the first Ignite Blood will wear off, so re Ignite Blood.  When your health gets to about 40-50% health, use bond to keep your health up.  If all goes well, your second Ignite Blood will wear off at around 10-20% health.  Eventually, when it's low enough the Dooming Darkness will have him stopped.  At that point, Darkness is no longer necessary since without it he will only be moving as fast as he did with Darkness at full health.  However, he needs to ALWAYS be feared, he can kill your pet VERY VERY fast.  Also, do NOT underestimate his ability to riposte.  NPCs can still riposte while feared, and at level 50 his skills are very high, and he hits VERY hard.  I once lost a pet that was at around 25% health to riposte.  I thought he was fine because I was keeping him feared and he was already low health, this is the reason for Pact of Shadow.  Periodically, check your pets health, especially if you know after a Fear wore off that he tore pet up.  If he gets below 1/3 health use a Pact of Shadow and do an extra bond of death.<br><br>

Ideally, you should have him killed before Augment wears off.  It takes me usually about 5 minutes to kill him.  If Augment DOES wear off before he dies, don't worry.  It is not worth the danger of getting in close to re-augment pet, since you have to be REAL close to cast it, and he should be almost dead anyways.  The reason I use Dead Man Floating is that the island is basically one big hill, so you never have to worry about falling damage.  Its secondary value is that you can move straight off the hill where as Dino has to run up/down it.  This can give you the extra distance you need if he resists a ton of Darkness' in a row and it wears off and you need to re-Fear/Darkness.<br><br>

The respawn rate is VERY fast, I think its like 30 seconds.  So after you kill him, you will likely see him up again shortly.  If he doesn't spawn, than an Aqua Goblin Sacrifice spawned in his place.  When you are ready to do him again, just find the sacrifice and kill it.  Keep doing this till Dino spawns.  He can spawn anywhere on island so make sure you med on coast, and after you kill sacrifice, run to coast and wait about a minute before you go looking.<br><br>

Most of the time he drops nothing, or snake scales and lizard meat, worthless.  Rarely he can drop The highest value rare gems and 49 research.  But be prepared for disappointment.  I have done him around 30 times and only got 1 Necro word, and a small number of Wizard/Mage/Enchanter items.  Some jacinths, a ruby, and a few pieces of jewelry that sold from 130-200 pp.  So, when he does drop something its well worth it.  Also, the length of time it takes to kill him makes the XP trivial.  If you are just looking for some XP and decent loot, go kill Seafuries.  You will make out FAR better in both departments.</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:gohan@asapnet.net'>Matamkin</td></tr><tr></table><br><br></table></div>